The paper deals with fault diagnosis in hybrid systems, which are systems that mix continuous and discrete behaviors. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses game theory to model the fault diagnosis problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the computation of winning strategies, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The use of diagnosers and the detection of faults suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses hybrid automata as a modeling framework, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
